{{spanish name 2|Obiang|Avomo}} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Pedro Obiang | image = Obiang West Ham 2015.jpg | image_size = 200 | caption = Obiang warming up for [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] in 2015 | fullname = Pedro Mba Obiang Avomo<ref name=BDFutbol>{{cite web |url=https://www.bdfutbol.com/en/j/j19728.html |title=Pedro Mba: Pedro Mba Obiang Avomo: Player |publisher=BDFutbol |accessdate=4 May 2018}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1992|3|27|df=y}}<ref name=BDFutbol/> | birth_place = [[Alcalá de Henares]], Spain | height = 1.85 m<ref name=BDFutbol/> | position = [[Midfielder]] | currentclub = [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] | clubnumber = 14 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[Atlético Madrid]] | youthyears2 = 2008–2010 | youthclubs2 = [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] | years1 = 2010–2015 | clubs1 = [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] | caps1 = 128 | goals1 = 4 | years2 = 2015– | clubs2 = [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] | caps2 = 84 | goals2 = 3 | nationalyears1 = 2009 | nationalteam1 = [[Spain national under-17 football team|Spain U17]] | nationalcaps1 = 2 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2011 | nationalteam2 = [[Spain national under-19 football team|Spain U19]] | nationalcaps2 = 3 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalyears3 = 2013–2014 | nationalteam3 = [[Spain national under-21 football team|Spain U21]] | nationalcaps3 = 2 | nationalgoals3 = 0 | nationalyears4 = 2018– | nationalteam4 = [[Equatorial Guinea national football team|Equatorial Guinea]] | nationalcaps4 = 1 | nationalgoals4 = 0 | club-update = 21:14, 9 February 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 18 November 2018 (UTC) }} '''Pedro Mba Obiang Avomo''' (born 27 March 1992) is a Spanish-born Equatoguinean professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for English club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] and the [[Equatorial Guinea national football team|Equatorial Guinea national team]]. He had previously played for [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]], before moving to London, and the [[Premier League]], in 2015. Obiang has represented Spain at [[Spain national under-17 football team|under-17]], [[Spain national under-19 football team|under-19]] and [[Spain national under-21 football team|under-21]] levels before switching to represent the [[Equatorial Guinea national football team]].
==Club career== ===Sampdoria=== Born in [[Alcalá de Henares]], in the [[Community of Madrid]],<ref name=BDFutbol/> Obiang began his football career playing for various teams from his home city such CD Avance, [[RSD Alcalá]] and AD Naya, where he excelled. Due to these participations, he was transferred to the Cadete team of [[Atlético Madrid]]. He left Atlético for [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] in 2008 at age 16, the minimum age that international transfer within the [[European Union]] is allowed. He was the member of ''Allievi Nazionali'' youth team in 2008–09 season, but also call-up to the first team in pre-season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sampdoria.it/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=3690&Itemid=38|title=Fornaroli presente, la Samp segna sei gol al Chiasso |date=4 September 2008|accessdate=16 September 2010|work=UC Sampdoria|language=Italian}}</ref> He was also an unused substitute against [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]] and against [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]], by the decision of head coach [[Walter Mazzarri]]. In 2009–10, he was promoted to senior youth team&nbsp;– [[Campionato Nazionale Primavera|Primavera]].
Primary a youth team player, Obiang also played seven times in pre-season friendlies in summer 2010, scoring two goals. After the injury crisis of the Genoese team in which the team lost midfielders [[Stefano Guberti]], [[Fernando Tissone]], [[Andrea Poli]] and [[Paolo Sammarco]], he received a call-up again from new head coach [[Domenico Di Carlo]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sampdoria.it/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=6948&Itemid=38|title=Ventuno convocati: il Pazzo ce la fa, Guberti resta a casa|date=11 September 2010|accessdate=16 September 2010|work=UC Sampdoria|language=Italian}}</ref> and made his competitive debut on 12 September 2010. He substituted [[Vladimir Koman]] in the 58th minute, at that time Sampdoria losing 1–2 to [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]; eventually, Sampdoria 3–3 draw at [[Stadio Olimpico di Torino]]. Obiang signed a new, five-year contract extension with Doria on the morning before the start of the match.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sampdoria.it/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=6957&Itemid=38|title=Il d.g. Gasparin: "Carattere e alternative di qualità"|date=12 September 2010|accessdate=16 September 2010|work=UC Sampdoria|language=Italian}}</ref>
Obiang also named in [[2010–11 UEFA Champions League]] 25-men senior squad (list A) for play-off round and received the call-up against [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sampdoria.it/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=6842&Itemid=38|title=Poli non-ce la fa, ventidue i convocati per il Werder |date=23 August 2010|accessdate=16 September 2010|work=UC Sampdoria|language=Italian}}</ref> however Obiang was not named as one of players on the substitutes' bench. He also received his first call-up for [[2010–11 UEFA Europa League]] on 28 September 2010 as list B players (Under-21 youth product).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sampdoria.it/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=7061&Itemid=38|title=Venti convocati per il Debrecen, in lista torna Tissone|date=29 September 2010|accessdate=30 September 2010|work=UC Sampdoria|language=Italian}}</ref> He made his European debut on 16 December 2010 (matchday 6), with the club already eliminated before the match, a 0–2 defeat to [[Debreceni VSC|Debreceni]].
===West Ham United=== On 10 June 2015, [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] announced the signing of Obiang for an undisclosed fee on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.whufc.com/News/Articles/2015/June/10-June/Hammers-obtain-Obiang? | title=Hammers obtain Obiang | publisher=West Ham United F.C. | accessdate=10 June 2015}}</ref> He made his [[Premier League]] debut on 15 August as a half-time substitute for [[Reece Oxford]] in a 1–2 home defeat to [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bevan|first1=Chris|title=West Ham 1–2 Leicester|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33832171|accessdate=16 August 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=16 August 2015}}</ref> In November 2016, Obiang was announced as West Ham's Player of the Month for October.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2016/november/09-november/payet-wins-goal-month |title=Payet wins Goal of the Month |publisher=West Ham United F.C. |accessdate=22 November 2016}}</ref>
On 4 February 2017, Obiang scored his first Premier League goal for ''the Hammers'' on his 55th appearance for the club, against [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]]. The ball fell to Obiang from a corner, where he controlled, and then shot finding the bottom corner from 25 yards out.{{citation needed|date=March 2017}} On 20 March 2017, he was ruled out for the remainder of the [[2016–17 West Ham United F.C. season|2016–17 season]], having rolled his ankle during a home defeat by Leicester on 18 March 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportinglife.com/football/news/obiang-ruled-out-for-season/46960 |title=West Ham's Pedro Obiang ruled out for season |work=Sporting Life |accessdate=20 March 2017}}</ref> In January 2018, Obiang was injured during an [[FA Cup]] game against [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]]. In February he underwent knee surgery and was ruled out for the remainder of the 2017–18 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/pedro-obiang-set-to-miss-remainder-of-the-season-after-west-ham-star-undergoes-knee-surgery-a3758236.html|title=Obiang set to miss rest of the season after knee surgery|publisher=}}</ref>
==International career== Obiang has been capped for Spain at youth levels. Obiang received a call up for Porto International Tournament in April 2011.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rfef.es/index.jsp?nodo=39&ID=3308 |title=Convocatoria para el Torneo Internacional de Oporto |date=12 April 2011 |accessdate=6 May 2012 |work=RFEF |language=Spanish |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110517071725/http://www.rfef.es/index.jsp?nodo=39&ID=3308 |archivedate=17 May 2011 }}</ref>
Due to his [[Beti-Pahuin peoples#Fang|Fang]] background, the [[Gabonese Football Federation]] tried unsuccessfully to persuade Obiang to play for [[Gabon national football team|Gabon]], although both his parents and his grandparents are from [[Equatorial Guinea]]. In November 2011, they included him in a squad list for a match between [[Gabon national under-20 football team|the country's under-20]] and [[China PR national under-20 football team|China]], however he ignored the call.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.les-pantheres.com/site/index.php?option%3Dcom_content%26view%3Darticle%26id%3D1463%3Aliste-des-preselectionnes-u20-gabon-vs-chine-du-27-novembre-2011-a-libreville%26catid%3D48%3Afootball%26Itemid%3D78 |title=Liste des présélectionnés U20 (Gabon vs Chine) du 27 novembre 2011 à Libreville| accessdate=20 November 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419065232/http://www.les-pantheres.com/site/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1463:liste-des-preselectionnes-u20-gabon-vs-chine-du-27-novembre-2011-a-libreville&catid=48:football&Itemid=78 |archivedate=19 April 2012 }}</ref>
Being eligible to represent [[Equatorial Guinea national football team|Equatorial Guinea]], in 2011, [[Equatoguinean Football Federation|the country's federation]] approached Obiang to enquire if he would be willing to represent the country at the [[2012 Africa Cup of Nations]], however Obiang declined.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.libertaddigital.com/deportes/futbol/2013-11-15/perico-obiang-el-sobrino-del-dictador-que-rechaza-jugar-con-guinea-ecuatorial-1276504256/|title=Perico Obiang, el sobrino del dictador que juega en la Sampdoria|publisher=Libertad Digital|date=15 November 2013|accessdate=6 September 2016|language=Spanish}}</ref> In April 2015, after a meeting with the Equatoguinean Football Federation people, Obiang's stance on representing Equatorial Guinea appeared to have changed after showing a desire to play for the country.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.guineaecuatorialpress.com/noticia.php?id=6430|title=Reunión de la Feguifut con Perico Mba Obiang|publisher=guineaecuatorialpress.com|date=13 April 2015|accessdate=6 September 2016|language=Spanish}}</ref> On 5 October 2016, Obiang reunited in London with Equatoguinean Football Federation president Andrés Mbomio, and Equatoguinean national team head coach and coordinator [[Esteban Becker]] and [[Juvenal Edjogo-Owono]] respectively to reach an agreement.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.feguifut.org/noticia/reunion-cumbre-del-presidente-de-la-feguifut-y-pedro-obiang|title=Reunión cumbre del Presidente de la FEGUIFUT y Pedro Obiang|publisher=[[Equatoguinean Football Federation]]|date=6 October 2016|accessdate=7 October 2016|language=Spanish}}</ref>
On 7 November 2018, Obiang was officially called up for the Equatorial Guinea national team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.feguifut.org/noticia/convocatoria-nzalang-nacional|title=Convocatoria Nzalang Nacional|language=es|date=7 November 2018|accessdate=8 November 2018|publisher=FEGUIFUT}}</ref> Obiang made his debut for Equatorial Guinea in a 1–0 loss to [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]] on 18 November 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2018/november/19-november/obiang-makes-equatorial-guinea-debut|title=Obiang makes Equatorial Guinea debut - West Ham United|website=www.whufc.com}}</ref> In December 2018 he said he was "proud" to play for the nation.<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46632747</ref>
